The paper deals with the channel coding problem, which is a fundamental problem in information theory and communication engineering. The paper uses optimization techniques to derive a minimax-converse for the problem, which is a common approach in information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with the computation of the bound, which involves algorithmic and computational aspects, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) another likely category. The paper also involves the study of properties of the converse, which can be related to the study of properties of optimization problems, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) possible categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of optimization techniques to derive bounds, which can be related to the study of optimization problems in machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category as well.
